<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="359" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/661.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-19"><hi rend="italic">August 19,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The minister says he will recognize the Government of Gen. Leconte, in
                            accordance with the Department’s instructions, and suggests that in the
                            course of the day an American warship be instructed to fire a
                            salute.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>